Most of the GC was coming from creating empty hashmap

like this

Map modelToEditPart = new HashMap();
or
Map mapModelToEditPart = new HashMap();


and from creating empty arraylists

List trash = new ArrayList ();

On profiling the code we found in most cases Map as well as the List were never used

mainly because 

connections would be Collections$EmptyList 
or 
modelObjects would be an empty list

You can probably save on the memory used by GEF code

also just noticing

	//Remove the remaining Connection EditParts
	List trash = new ArrayList ();
	for (; i < connections.size(); i++)
		trash.add(connections.get(i));
	for (i = 0; i < trash.size(); i++)
		removeTargetConnection((ConnectionEditPart)trash.get(i));

why is the list being created

- added Scriptable scope to the signature of the IMonkeyDOMFactory.getDOMroot() method
- passing in scope now allows DOM extensions to add global JS objects that can be instantiated
- added a new DOM extension, io, whos init method created 2 new JS objects, File and WebRequest
-File object enables local file i/o (i.e. read/write/create)  sample included
- WebRequest enables getting of text from a specified URL (GET or POST)  sample included

